        "timestamp": "2021-05-20 15:22:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> so merging this should mean that the final step of moving tosca-poc back into master should not have much to review?  if we still have to review a bunch, then this isn't buying us much, is it?  However, if it does reduce the amount to review in the final step, then it's probably the \"right\" way to do it.\n\nAll of the content in this review has already been submitted by Seb and Martial in Master so it is already reviewed. \n\nThis review brings tosca-poc up to the level of master. So, apart from the stuff in the tosca-controlloop directory, there will be no difference between the master and tosca-poc after this review goes through. (Well the only difference is the INFO.yaml file, which I didn't know until today has to be submitted in a separate review).\n\nThe next review will move the tosca-poc code from the modules in tosca-controlloop into the modules directly in master. That review will be moving around files that are already reviewed, so again it is reviewed code.\n\nThe final review will merge the tosca-poc branch into master, and again, that is all reviewed code.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
